description:
The trainee is expected to participate in one of the following research work/projects: 
(1) Robot-assisted non-destructive detection of tile defects on building exteriors;
(2) Vision-language model-enhanced human-robot collaboration in construction;	
(3) Knowledge-driven intelligent quality management system for off-site construction.

A student will work at the company chemical laboratory and engaged in the following duties:
- Analysis of raw materials and (semi-) finished products based on organoleptic, physico-chemical and microbiological indicators;
- Determination of density, moistness, amount of dry matter of the raw materials, such as wheat or corn;
- Quality control of the (semi-) finished products.

The detailed work-plan will be sent upon receipt of nomination documents.
